Description: Body sherd of Chian black-figured pottery Komast chalice; white slip; interior glazed; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of part of female figure's garment with squares and added red.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see Lemos no. 1468 from Emporio.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.1288) (phase 2)
